<paragraph id="8B93368F4220FFF698537F6CAA13FA9E" blockId="28.[806,1422,1299,1505]" box="[806,893,1299,1320]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B958EA9D4220FFF698537F6CAA13FA9E" box="[806,893,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remark</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B93368F4220FFF698537F4DAD8AFA57" blockId="28.[806,1422,1299,1505]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D0C4220FFF698537F4DAD04FAF1" authorityName="Mulaik" authorityYear="1960" box="[806,1130,1330,1351]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scleropactidae" genus="Spherarmadillo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavernicola">
<emphasis id="B958EA9D4220FFF698537F4DAD04FAF1" box="[806,1130,1330,1351]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Spherarmadillo cavernicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reduced to a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D0C4220FFF698E57F2EAD78FAD0" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1907" box="[912,1046,1361,1382]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scleropactidae" genus="Spherarmadillo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarzi">
<emphasis id="B958EA9D4220FFF698E57F2EAD78FAD0" box="[912,1046,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. schwarzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B7E4220FFF69F327F2EAD9DFAD1" author="Schultz GA" box="[1095,1267,1361,1383]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="3 - 14" refId="ref83271" refString="Schultz GA. 1984. Three new and five other species of Oniscoidea from Belize, Central America (Crustacea, Isopoda). Journal of Natural History 18: 3 - 14." type="journal article" year="1984">Schultz (1984)</bibRefCitation>
. The present investigation suggests that these are separate species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D0C4220FFF698537FF1AD3EFA15" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1907" box="[806,1104,1422,1443]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scleropactidae" genus="Spherarmadillo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarzi">
<emphasis id="B958EA9D4220FFF698537FF1AD3EFA15" box="[806,1104,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Spherarmadillo schwarzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D0C4220FFF69E0D7FF1AAC9FA74" authorityName="Mulaik" authorityYear="1960" class="Malacostraca" family="Scleropactidae" genus="Spherarmadillo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavernicola">
<emphasis id="B958EA9D4220FFF69E0D7FF1AAC9FA74" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. cavernicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at least by the serrated margin of the pleon epimera and uropod sympodites.
</paragraph>
